Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon}, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Peel @garlic{1%clove} and wrap clove in a small piece of #foil{}; place on same sheet. Roast on top rack, flipping potatoes halfway through, until tender and garlic is softened, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> TIP: If garlic is done before potatoes, remove from baking sheet and continue roasting potatoes.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}. Dice @Roma Tomato{1}. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a large pan over medium heat. Add onion; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir in tomato, half the @balsamic vinegar{5%teaspoon} (use all for 4 servings), and @sugar{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4). Cook, stirring, until softened and jammy, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside. Wipe out pan.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce} and remaining Fry Seasoning. Form into two wide, roughly ½-inch-thick rounds (four rounds for 4 servings). Divide @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup} between centers of each round. Fold edges of meat around cheddar, shaping and sealing to create cheese-stuffed patties, each slightly wider than a burger bun. Season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for jam over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat.

While patties cook, halve @potato buns{2}; toast until golden brown. Once garlic is done, carefully open foil and mash clove with a #fork{} until smooth. In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, and mashed garlic. Season with salt and pepper.

Spread buns with @ketchup{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4 servings) and a thin layer of sauce. Fill buns with patties and tomato onion jam. Divide burgers and potatoes between plates. Serve with any remaining sauce on the side for dipping.